<Content>Brilliant position, great facilities, good value This is the second time we have stayed at the Hotel, and we were not disappointed. Last time (two years ago) we stayed in the Centre building, this time in the Monument building. Of the two, although the reception and common parts of the Monument building are better, the larger rooms (and the direct access to the roof top bar and pool) make the Centre building a better choice. The position, just across the road from Gaudi's 'La Pedrera' (an absolute 'must' to visit), on the stylish Passeig de Garcia, could not be better. The staff are helpful, and the rooms of a high quality. There is a small roof terrace pool at the top of the Monument building, but no bar or room service. On the eighth floor of the Centre building (just across the road) there is a wonderful, very 'cool', roof top bar and a small pool. Breakfast is extra (and quite expensive), but there are numerous places within five minutes to sample the delights of Barcelona's cafe culture.This is a really stylish place to base yourself, with many of Barcelona's sights in walking distance, and close to a major hub in the Metro system 
