<Content>Nice bed and breakfast - but that's about the only nice thing!!! We booked this hotel via easyjet and were not informed of the rennovation works by either easyjet or through looking at the hotel's own web site.We arrived at 12 noon but were unable to check in, even though a man arriving 15 mins after us was allowed to. We were put in the modern side of the hotel, which we later found out wasn't a good thing! We arrived back at 8:30pm after a long day of sight seeing and were given a room where the TV was broken. We contacted reception who told us there was nothing that could be done until the next day and after a drawn out 45 mins begrudgingly gave us a room next door.The room was ok and a good size, the bed very comfy. However the shower leaked every time you used it and required 4 bath towels to mop up the floor, the sinks sprayed water everywhere, the lighting in the room was terrible and you couldn't open any windows. There was a huge blind which once was up allowed everyone to see in from opposite buildings. The room was clean though the workmanship from the rennovations was poor and shoddy quality.The location is great - very central to most areas.I agree with the previous reports, the majority of the reception staff could really seem to care less about guests. Requests for assistance were provided, but grudgingly. There is no concierge service. They refused to call taxis for us and when we asked them to book one for our return trip to the airport we actually saw them flag one down for us (i.e. they never pre-booked it). They gave us no information about the hotel upon check-in (i.e., location of the restaurant, hours of dining, hours of the piano bar, pool bar, etc) and we didn't even know there was a lounge/bar area until we walked to the other building to look for ourselves. This is not a four star hotel on the newly rennovated side and there are definitely nicer places to stay!!! 
